From {{inh|en|enm|kin}}, {{m|enm|kyn}}, {{m|enm|ken}}, {{m|enm|kun}}, from {{inh|en|ang|cynn||kind, sort, rank, quality, family, generation, offspring, pedigree, kin, race, people, gender, sex, propriety, etiquette}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*kunją||race, generation, descent}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro||*ǵn̥h₁yom}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*ǵenh₁-||to produce}}. Cognate with {{cog|sco|kin||relatives, kinfolk}}, {{cog|frr|kinn}}, {{m|frr|kenn||gender, race, family, kinship}}, {{cog|nl|kunne||gender, sex}}, {{cog|gml|kunne||gender, sex, race, family, lineage}}, Danish {{m|da|køn||gender, sex}}, Swedish {{m|sv|kön||gender, sex}}, {{cog|is|kyn||gender}}, and through Indo-European, with Latin {{m|la|genus||kind, sort, ancestry, birth}}, Ancient Greek {{m|grc|γένος||kind, race}}, Albanian {{m|sq|dhen||(herd of) small cattle}}.

